      "note": "Optical single-AP FWHM digitized from the mean ± SEM spike waveform in Fig. 1I (right sub-panel, the salmon positive-going pAceR trace; narrow spike on a flat baseline), recorded in awake mouse V1 VIP+ interneurons in vivo under 1P epifluorescence at 400 Hz with 4×4 binning. FWHM measured at half of the peak ΔF/F deflection, calibrated to the panel's 5 ms scale bar (35 px = 5 ms). At 400 Hz the frame interval is 2.5 ms, so this width is frame-rate-broadened — treat it as an upper bound on the intrinsic optical response (underlying step kinetics τ ≈ 3.8/4.1 ms). Companion waveforms in the same panel: Ace-mNeon2, pAce, VARNAM2."
